# Common Rules — Limerence Workspace

## Comments & Documentation — Preserve, Don't Delete

When editing code, **preserving existing documentation has higher priority** than «cleaning up» comments. Removing a comment without explicit user request is a regression.

### Never Remove (Unless Behavior Was Deleted)

| Kind | Example |
|------|---------|
| File-level JSDoc | `@file`, `@description`, `@component` |
| Spec links | `@see Спецификация/...` or `@see docs/...` |
| Field / prop docs | `/** Рамка после resolveDialogFrame */` |
| «Why» inline comments | timing, race, layout jump, fallback, guard reason |
| `eslint-disable` / `eslint-disable-next-line` | only if the lint rule still applies |

### Refactoring — Migrate, Don't Drop

When replacing a block (rename, extract, move):

1. Re-attach field JSDoc to the new symbol
2. Move `@see` links to the new file if logic moved
3. Update wording if behavior changed; do not silently delete

### What to Add (New Code Only)

- Gameplay / product logic → spec in `docs/specs/` or `docs/gameplay/` + `@see` in JSDoc
- Non-obvious implementation → short «why» comment; link to spec, don't paste spec prose

---

## Спецификация — Implementation Workflow

**Source of truth:** `docs/specs/` (mirror of `mobile/Спецификация/`). Code must match spec; spec must reflect intentional code changes.

**Contract for deletion:** anything not documented in specs is candidate for removal.

### Spec Before Code (Mandatory for Gameplay)

1. **Identify** entity doc (`Диалог.md`, `Сцена.md`, …) in `docs/specs/` or `docs/gameplay/`
2. **Describe** behavior, state transitions, edge cases
3. **Implement** with `@see docs/specs/...` or `@see Спецификация/...` (symlink)
4. **Remove** code paths the updated spec no longer mentions

**Same task:** spec update + code change together.

### Entity Index

| Entity | Spec path |
|--------|-----------|
| Dialog | `docs/specs/Логика геймлея/Сущности/Диалог.md` |
| Dialog frame | `docs/specs/Логика геймлея/Сущности/РамкаДиалога.md` |
| Scene | `docs/specs/Логика геймплея/Сущности/Сцена.md` |
| Character | `docs/specs/Логика геймплея/Сущности/Персонаж.md` |
| Chapter | `docs/specs/Логика геймплея/Сущности/Глава.md` |
| Gameplay overview | `docs/specs/Логика геймплея/Логика геймплея.md` |
| Tech architecture | `docs/specs/Техническая документация.md` |
| Monetization BR | `docs/product/monetization/Paywall.md` |
| Monetization domain | `docs/monetization/` |

### Spec globs

This rule also applies when editing: `docs/**/*.md`, `mobile/Спецификация/**/*.md`

### Anti-Patterns

- Gameplay code without spec update
- Keeping dead branches when spec no longer mentions them
- `@deprecated` wrappers instead of deleting obsolete paths
